VTo celebrate World Music Day on a grand scale, the employees of Visakha Steel Plant organised a concert of carnatic music last Sunday. Inaugurated by CMD-RINL P.K. Bishnoi, the concert was held at a hall at Ukkunagaram Township.The vocalist duo Shanmukhapriya and Haripriya, who started learning carnatic music from their father, V.V. Subbaram,and laterunder the expert tutelage of the renowned Kalaimanis Radha and Jayalakshmi, performed at the venue.The duo achieved repute as Priya sisters first at theSpirit of Freedomconcerts conducted in Delhi in 1990. They have been conferred the M.S. Subbalakshmi memorial award by Visakha Music Academy in the port city last year. Admirably supported on the violin by M.A. Krishnaswamy and on mridangam by N.S. Subrahmanyam and M. Murali on the ghatam, the sisters regaled the audience for two hours.After getting warmed up renderingSaami Dayachooda(Kedaragowla),Varavallabha(Hamsadhwani),Mundu Venuka(Darbar) with swaram andNannuvidachi(Reethigowla) prefixed with aalapana also in turns, they renderedAmajavaragamawith invigorating and scintillating swaram.Then after absorbingly singingDevadideva(Sunaadavinodini) with refreshing aalapana, neravu and swaram in turns andKamalaambaof Syama Sastry, they expansively elaboratedPaalinchu Kaamakshi(Madhyamavathi). Their expression ofManodharmaby way of ragalapana, neravu and swaram, a treat by itself was rendered wholesome by the thani executed thrillingly by Subrahmanyam on the mridangam. It was ably supplemented on ghatam by Murali.
